FBIS3-49646 "dreeu009_s_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 SLOVENIA Controversy Over Krsko Nuclear Plant Reported Government Discusses Relations AU1201205294 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 1800 GMT 12 Jan 94 AU1201205294 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network Language: Slovene Article Type:BFN [Text] The Slovene Government has today done everything with a view to settling relations between our state and the neighboring Croatia. Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek has assembled all ministers in order to coordinate views on some issues regarding relations between the neighbors -- ranging from the Krsko nuclear power plant to the joint border. The general secretary of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs announced a high level meeting between the two countries. At that meeting, the (?prime ministers) will coordinate mutual relations. In this connection, let us add that shortly before 1530 the gradual connection of the nuclear power plant to the surroundings has begun.
